Welcome to the Self Paced 'Logical Thinking and Communication' Toolkit. The intent of this toolkit is to improve our ability to structure our thoughts and communicate them effectively, to be the best communicator version, of ourselves, that we can be! Contributions welcome.


Top things you should be comfortable with at the end of this workshop:
      * Understand your audience
      * Understand the Why, What and How model 
      * Understand the "Lean Startup” philosophy"
      * Master Win-Win negotiation concepts 
      * Learn details about body language 
      * Understand the Art of Storytelling 
      * Give a public speech of 5 to 10 mins (example a toastmasters setting)
      * Writing Critical emails
      * Take the most complex technical/scientific topic you know and write a blog, explaining that topic to a 8 year old
      * Speak impromptu for 5 mins. Audience size has to be 30 + people


