Month 3:
      * Proactive Communication: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tex0zKuLCMg
      * Personal Introductions:
            * Practice how to speak your name right (last session’s video)
            * Create a three liner introduction, first line is your name, second line is who you are, third line is about adjusting the intro to the context
            * Who you are is not about your current role (developer/accountant/tester), or your job, or your relation or gender (father/mother/man/woman) or number of years at a company, but more about the essence of you.
                  * https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/shift-mind/201006/who-am-i
                  * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=trqDnLNRuSc
                  * Extra Credit: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ship_of_Theseus and https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UHwVyplU3Pg
            * At this point you should be atleast half way thru “Getting to Yes”, about 80 pages in. The next session on 14th June, will be dedicated to ‘Getting to Yes’
            * Think thru and unicast me the BIGGEST challenge that you face when you communicate
            * Research ‘Lean Startup’ principles (Entrepreneurial Mindset/Entrepreneurship Mgmt/Validated Learning/Innovation Accounting/(Build/Measure/Learn)/Lean Canvas). Majority of the session will be spent on the Lean Startup: https://www.usertesting.com/blog/2015/12/11/how-to-implement-the-lean-startup-at-large-organizations/


Month 4:
      * We will start delving into Body Language and its impact on communication
            * https://www.ted.com/talks/amy_cuddy_your_body_language_shapes_who_you_are
            * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rk_SMBIW1mg
            * https://www.ted.com/talks/ron_gutman_the_hidden_power_of_smiling
            * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZK3jSXYBNak
            * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w-HYZv6HzAs
      * The unwritten rule of introducing people: How to introduce people: http://www.wikihow.com/Introduce-People
      * “Getting to Yes” book Discussion - with your team
      * Its all about applying the learnings and practice!
            a.	Making an impromptu speech (content & mental mindset) 
            b.	Engaging communication 
            c. 	Vocabulary 
            d.	Larger Audience - Fear of forgetting 
            e.	Talking to an aggressive person 
            f.  Clarity of communication 
            g.	Purchasing a new Item (Negotiations) 
            h.	Introduce yourself to a new person (colleague) 
            i.  Pace of speech
            j.  Making small talk 
 

 
Month 5:
      Practice: 
          * Impromptu speech
          * Understanding the question/topic in any discussion
          * Applying generic models to reason your way to an effective frame
          * Shaping the thoughts
          * Putting it all together in words and body language
          * Writing effectively
          * Different forms of writing
          * Differentiating between Chat apps VS email VS in person VS in group meeting VS speech
          * Following efficient communication principles, especially for Chat Apps (nohello.com/nohello.net)
               * https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=omuzBQaPQjw&t=26s
          * Improving Vocabulary
          * Different written mediums (email/messengers/wiki/jam/BB/forums) and their rules


Month 6: 
      * The big speech
      * The big email
      * The big blog
      * Table Top sessions (delivering small 1 to 2 mins unprepared speeches in an articulate manner)

 
 

 
 


















 

